<div id="pf682" class="pf w1c h125" data-page-no="682"><div class="pc pc682 w1c h125"><div class="t m25c x2d h33 y20c0 ff1 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LIFE OF CHRIST. </div><div class="t m5 x58 h33 y20bb ff1 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m292 xbe h33 y20bc ff1 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">27 </div><div class="t m326 x27 h28 y15b2 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">daily reading of prayers and singing the &quot; Hallel,&quot;—&quot; Praise </div><div class="t m1ce x11 h28 yf1d ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ye Jehovah.&quot; Josephus says that the festival was also called </div><div class="t m31b x11 h28 y9eb ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot; Lights.&quot; </div><div class="t m167b x14 h28 yd37 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">z. There seemed but one retreat left for the persecuted Son of </div><div class="t m93f x11 h28 ydae ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God. He had been rejected in Galilee, and now in Judea His hte </div><div class="t m582 x11 h28 ybaf ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">was threatened. But His life was yet to be extended. Jerusalem </div><div class="t m1956 x11 h28 yacf ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">was the only place where fanatical zeal abounded enough to put to </div><div class="t mf42 x11 h28 y9b2 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">death such a being (Luke 13 : 34). So Jesus retired temporarily </div><div class="t m4cc x11 h28 ya8b ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to the half-heathen country of Perea, east of the Jordan. </div><div class="t m139 x14 h28 yb0d ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t med x36 h28 yc02 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Moses had said that on certain considerations, divorce was </div><div class="t m674 x11 h28 y7d1 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lawful. The rabbis had so construed the Hebrew word used by </div><div class="t mafa x11 h28 yb78 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Moses to convey the cause for divorce, as to make it cover the </div><div class="t m567 x11 h28 y157d ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">most frivolous excuse. The whole thing, however, seems to be </div><div class="t m5e5 x11 h28 y56b ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">summed up in this: If one saw any other woman which pleased </div><div class="t m686 x11 h28 y2085 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">him more than his wife, the excuse for divorce was an easy matter. </div><div class="t m2f6 x11 h28 yf30 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In the eagerness of the Pharisees to tempt Christ, and to entangle </div><div class="t ma2 x11 h28 y841 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Him in His talk, they pressed the matter upon Him. But the </div><div class="t m312 x11 h28 yff8 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lord&apos;s answer was discreet and silencing, and they failed in their </div><div class="t mea2 x11 h28 y933 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">object. It seems that, having determined on the death of Christ, </div><div class="t m2f5 x11 h28 y526 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and desiring to shield themselves before the people from the charge </div><div class="t m1654 x11 h28 y12d4 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of putting Him to death, the question was put at that time, and in </div><div class="t m19e3 x11 h28 yb80 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the studied form it was, that it might involve Christ in the difficulty </div><div class="t m77a x11 h28 y988 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">which caused the death of John the Baptist. Herod Antipas, in </div><div class="t md27 x11 h28 yd60 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">whose dominion Christ was then staying, was a noted adulterer, </div><div class="t m1f0 x11 h28 yf44 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and if Christ could be drawn into a position which would be a </div><div class="t m865 x11 h28 y9f6 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">condemnation of Herod&apos;s course, that ruler might be induced to </div><div class="t m162d x11 h28 y157f ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">put the hated Nazarene out of the way. </div><div class="t m13e x5d h28 ya99 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t mbe8 x36 h28 ya99 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ told the disciples, in substance, that all men could not </div><div class="t mc6 x11 h28 y1470 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">receive their idea of the question. There were some, indeed, who </div><div class="t m1dfd x11 h28 y1031 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">must live single lives by circumstances of birth, or constitution; and </div><div class="t m47c x11 h28 ybbd ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">some because of the mutilation endured through the cruel practises </div><div class="t md27 x11 h28 yffc ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of bond-masters. Others there were of this class who, by special </div><div class="t mb94 x11 h28 yc85 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">vow, had withdrawn themselves from society for the kingdom of </div><div class="t m1184 x11 h28 yd2c ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">heaven&apos;s sake. These were not better than others, but simply </div><div class="t m1147 x11 h28 ybc0 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">different.&apos; The marriage institution was created by Christ in Eden </div><div class="t mcfd x11 h28 y5ac ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for a wise purpose, and must still be necessary, even though sin </div><div class="t m1857 x11 h28 y11ff ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">has overspread the world. 1 Cor. 7 : 2. </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
